1 5.6. "Appraisal report" means any communication of an appraisal.
2 6.7. "Appraisal subcommittee" means the appraisal subcommittee of the federal financial
3 institutions examination council.
4 7.8. "Appraiser" means a person who engages in appraisal activity for valuable
5 consideration.
6 8.9. "Apprentice appraiser" means a person who holds a valid permit as an apprentice
7 appraiser.
8 9.10. "Board" means the North Dakota real estate appraiser qualifications and ethics board.
9 10.11. "Certified appraiser" means a person who holds a valid permit as a certified residential
10 or general appraiser.
11 11.12. "Certified general appraiser" means a person who holds a valid permit as a certified
12 general appraiser.
13 12.13. "Certified residential appraiser" means a person who holds a valid permit as a certified
14 residential appraiser.
15 14. "Evaluation" means an estimate of the value of real property for use in a federally
16 related real estate financial transaction for which an appraisal is not required by
17 federal law.
18 13.15. "Licensed appraiser" means a person who holds a valid permit as a licensed
19 appraiser.
20 14.16. "Permit" means the document issued by the board, verifying that the person named on
21 the permit has fulfilled all prerequisites to practice either as an apprentice appraiser, a
22 licensed appraiser, or a certified appraiser.
23 15.17. "Real estate" means an identified parcel or tract of land including improvements, and
24 interests, benefits, and rights inherent in the ownership of real estate.
25 16.18. "Uniform standards of professional appraisal practices" means standards of appraisal
26 promulgated by the appraisal standards board of the appraisal foundation as adopted
27 by the board.
28 17.19. "Valuation" means an estimate of the value of real estate or real property.
